1
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:43,840
=No Pain No Gain=
(Adapted from the Qidian novel)

2
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:47,180
("Losing Money to Be a Tycoon"
by Qingshan Quzui)

3
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,220
=Episode 18=
(This story is purely fictional)

4
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:11,300
(Party A, Mediator)

5
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:33,140
It's you again.

6
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,140
The person involved is now saying

7
00:02:35,140 --> 00:02:36,946
you're impersonating
a designated driver.

8
00:02:40,670 --> 00:02:42,110
You're suspected of reckless driving.

9
00:02:42,390 --> 00:02:43,270
Tell us the situation.

10
00:02:43,550 --> 00:02:44,230
Sir,

11
00:02:44,230 --> 00:02:45,830
that's not the situation.

12
00:02:45,830 --> 00:02:46,550
You see, it's...

13
00:02:46,550 --> 00:02:47,790
Be more serious about it.

14
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:49,670
Sir,

15
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:50,230
the situation

16
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:51,700
isn't like what he described.

17
00:02:52,390 --> 00:02:53,110
Let me show you.

18
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:55,670
I've been a designated driver
for quite some time.

19
00:02:55,670 --> 00:02:57,990
And, I received a five-star review
on each of my trips.

20
00:02:58,010 --> 00:03:00,230
You see, there was even a client
who booked me monthly.

21
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,990
She wanted me
to pick her up every month.

22
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:03,830
But picking them up today?

23
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:05,580
That was the worst luck
I had in my life.

24
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:06,350
Don't you agree?

25
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,420
He likes to drive, huh?

26
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:09,270
You're lying!

27
00:03:09,510 --> 00:03:10,230
Sir,

28
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:11,420
our company

29
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:12,180
has always been

30
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:13,300
Tengda's

31
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:14,830
largest competitor.

32
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:16,300
Now, he's our designated driver.

33
00:03:16,391 --> 00:03:17,830
And, he almost caused an accident.

34
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:19,700
It's clear that he
was trying to murder us!

35
00:03:19,830 --> 00:03:20,670
He was!

36
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:21,580
Murder?

37
00:03:21,580 --> 00:03:23,270
That's nonsense,

38
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:23,900
don't you agree?

39
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:26,270
The traffic police
came to the scene as well.

40
00:03:26,270 --> 00:03:27,620
There's a dash cam in his car too.

41
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:29,830
What did the traffic police conclude?

42
00:03:29,830 --> 00:03:31,420
They concluded that, at worst,

43
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,420
I had merely made a driving error.

44
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:35,391
What murder? He thought
I wanted to murder him?

45
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:36,670
Why would I?

46
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:37,724
Let me ask you this, then.

47
00:03:37,746 --> 00:03:39,350
You're in charge of Tengda.

48
00:03:39,350 --> 00:03:41,350
Why did you join my company?

49
00:03:41,350 --> 00:03:43,280
And now, why are you
a designated driver?

50
00:03:43,302 --> 00:03:46,180
I joined Sky Fire purely
because I wanted to make money.

51
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,391
I'm being a designated driver

52
00:03:47,391 --> 00:03:48,580
purely because I want to try out

53
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:50,300
a different experience in life

54
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:51,180
and...

55
00:03:52,191 --> 00:03:53,746
And make some money while I'm at it.

56
00:03:54,790 --> 00:03:55,790
Make money?

57
00:04:12,950 --> 00:04:13,740
Your turn.

58
00:04:18,340 --> 00:04:21,580
(Police)

59
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:23,500
Sorry about that.

60
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,260
Sorry for the trouble. Thank you.

61
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:30,910
Well,

62
00:04:31,620 --> 00:04:33,180
the issue has been resolved perfectly.

63
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:35,470
Pei Qian,

64
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,500
you're lucky that I don't have

65
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:39,740
any evidence against you.

66
00:04:39,835 --> 00:04:41,150
But did you need to be this wary

67
00:04:41,670 --> 00:04:43,060
of me?

68
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:46,500
Did you need to do all that
just to assassinate me?

69
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:48,300
Assassinate you?

70
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:49,550
But don't worry.

71
00:04:49,550 --> 00:04:51,324
No matter what devious schemes you have,

72
00:04:51,620 --> 00:04:53,420
once Eternal Reincarnation is launched,

73
00:04:53,420 --> 00:04:54,710
I'll make sure Tengda

74
00:04:55,368 --> 00:04:56,680
suffers eternal damnation.

75
00:04:57,150 --> 00:04:58,300
Eternal damnation?

76
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,860
What the heck are you thinking?

77
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,300
Mr. Pei,

78
00:05:04,670 --> 00:05:05,420
don't worry.

79
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:06,420
I trust you.

80
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:08,119
I'm sure you won't commit
premeditated murder.

81
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:08,670
Yeah, right?

82
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:11,500
No one in their right mind
would believe that.

83
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,300
But...

84
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,924
I finally understood you chose
to become a designated driver.

85
00:05:16,180 --> 00:05:17,060
Why, then?

86
00:05:17,180 --> 00:05:17,860
Indeed.

87
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,180
People are at
their most relaxed state in the car.

88
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:23,102
Sometimes, they might blurt out
something they aren't supposed to.

89
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:24,350
This way,

90
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:28,620
it's easier to get a hold of
their confidential information.

91
00:05:28,635 --> 00:05:30,550
As the saying goes,
"Know the enemy and yourself,

92
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:31,820
join the battle personally,

93
00:05:31,820 --> 00:05:33,835
and you'll come up on top
with despicable means."

94
00:05:34,180 --> 00:05:35,300
Impressive.

95
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,260
I like that.

96
00:05:38,820 --> 00:05:39,500
See you.

97
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:43,060
What the heck is going on here?

98
00:05:44,124 --> 00:05:46,180
Mr. Pei, you took
the words out of my mouth.

99
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:47,860
What the heck is going on here?

100
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:49,670
Did you know

101
00:05:49,670 --> 00:05:51,820
what the police officer told me?

102
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:55,300
What?

103
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:57,230
He suggested
that I bring you to a psychiatrist.

104
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:01,030
Zhou Muyan was the one
who wasn't in his right mind.

105
00:06:01,030 --> 00:06:02,546
What has that got to do with me?

106
00:06:02,740 --> 00:06:03,350
Mr. Pei,

107
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:06,470
you signed a contract with Mr. Sima.

108
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,110
I know you have a mortgage to pay.

109
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:11,391
That's why you do part-time jobs
to make some pocket money.

110
00:06:11,413 --> 00:06:13,124
And, I'm turning a blind eye to it.

111
00:06:13,124 --> 00:06:14,350
But what do you mean by this?

112
00:06:14,635 --> 00:06:17,546
Are you getting a free 5,000-yuan salary
while being a designated driver?

113
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:18,910
Can you stop with

114
00:06:18,910 --> 00:06:20,060
all these ridiculous things?

115
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:22,124
I don't want to come
to the police station again.

116
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:25,060
Then what can I possibly do
that would lose me money?

117
00:06:26,140 --> 00:06:27,389
I finally figured it out.

118
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:29,500
All those unscrupulous capitalists
are all the same.

119
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,990
Mr. Sima,

120
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:33,380
Li Fuhui, Li Shi, and Zhou Muyan!

121
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:33,940
Listen up.

122
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:35,413
I'll work as a designated driver!

123
00:06:37,413 --> 00:06:38,380
I'll depend on myself.

124
00:06:38,380 --> 00:06:39,300
I'm not ashamed of it!

125
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:54,820
Morning.

126
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:55,857
- Morning.
- Morning.

127
00:06:55,857 --> 00:06:56,660
(Tengda Games)

128
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:01,060
Mr. Pei, you have
been reported by a client.

129
00:07:01,191 --> 00:07:02,500
After verification by the platform,

130
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,413
serious violations
have indeed been confirmed.

131
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,180
From today on,

132
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:07,910
your account and all accounts associated
with your real-name ID

133
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:08,910
will be banned.

134
00:07:09,213 --> 00:07:12,380
(Statistics on Revenues and Expenditures
for Each Settlement Period, The Culprit)

135
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:19,860
What's wrong?

136
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:20,940
Come here.

137
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:21,550
Hurry.

138
00:07:22,013 --> 00:07:24,230
When Mr. Pei returned
to his apartment last night,

139
00:07:24,230 --> 00:07:25,550
he looked very down.

140
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,470
After that, I bumped into Li Shi.

141
00:07:27,470 --> 00:07:28,860
Initially, I wanted to ignore him.

142
00:07:28,860 --> 00:07:30,791
But he actually knew why

143
00:07:30,813 --> 00:07:32,670
Mr. Pei became a designated driver.

144
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:34,620
Come here!

145
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,060
Come back! Don't keep us in suspense!

146
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:37,380
Finish the story!

147
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:39,790
Mr. Pei has infiltrated
the designated driver scene

148
00:07:39,790 --> 00:07:42,380
in hopes that he can
pick up Zhou Muyan one day

149
00:07:42,380 --> 00:07:45,420
and wait for him to blurt out all of his
company's confidential information.

150
00:07:49,550 --> 00:07:50,740
Something's off.

151
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,060
Sky Fire isn't located in Jinchuan.

152
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:55,150
This plan is utterly ineffective.

153
00:07:55,213 --> 00:07:57,520
Even if Mr. Pei works as
a designated driver all his life,

154
00:07:57,524 --> 00:07:58,902
he couldn't encounter Zhou Muyan.

155
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,250
No, that's not right.

156
00:08:03,257 --> 00:08:05,030
Huang Sibo has been
sharing tons of insights

157
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:06,635
on how to understand Pei with me lately.

158
00:08:06,657 --> 00:08:08,146
Although I couldn't learn them all,

159
00:08:08,191 --> 00:08:09,150
I did learn a few.

160
00:08:09,670 --> 00:08:10,350
You see,

161
00:08:10,670 --> 00:08:12,670
Mr. Pei did pick up
Zhou Muyan last night.

162
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,150
Sky Fire is under Fuhui, right?

163
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,260
Their HQ is located in Jinchuan, right?

164
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:22,500
Therefore, I'm sure
Mr. Pei has inside news.

165
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,991
He knew that Zhou Muyan
was coming here on a business trip.

166
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,420
Though old, the warhorse

167
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:30,060
still longs to gallop a thousand miles.

168
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,940
Mr. Pei is truly impressive.

169
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:34,660
Yeah.

170
00:09:00,860 --> 00:09:01,990
(Zhou Muyan,)

171
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:03,470
(you're too much.)

172
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:05,813
(I actually bumped into you
even as a designated driver.)

173
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:08,230
(I'll settle my debt with you later.)

174
00:09:08,230 --> 00:09:09,540
(Just you wait.)

175
00:09:14,020 --> 00:09:16,540
Mr. Pei, I've always
received a high wage.

176
00:09:16,635 --> 00:09:18,280
I usually pay other people 5,000 yuan

177
00:09:18,346 --> 00:09:19,780
for them to cover this task.

178
00:09:20,780 --> 00:09:21,900
About this,

179
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,710
I think it's kind of embarrassing.

180
00:09:23,710 --> 00:09:25,830
Why don't we forget it?

181
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:28,900
Madam,

182
00:09:29,380 --> 00:09:31,310
if you're outsourcing
this task to someone else,

183
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:32,740
that means you're very intelligent.

184
00:09:33,702 --> 00:09:35,230
It's the same no matter who you hire.

185
00:09:35,257 --> 00:09:36,470
You can hire me in the future.

186
00:09:36,470 --> 00:09:37,900
And, we're entrepreneurs.

187
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:39,950
We have to try out different
experiences in life.

188
00:09:41,110 --> 00:09:42,020
You see,

189
00:09:42,260 --> 00:09:43,710
we should forget about it.

190
00:09:44,140 --> 00:09:44,830
Let me do it.

191
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,140
Let me do it.

192
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:46,950
Let me do it.

193
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:48,260
Let me do it.

194
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:49,590
I told you already! Let me do it!

195
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:51,524
Madam, go and shop right now.

196
00:09:51,546 --> 00:09:52,990
It's the same no matter who you hire!

197
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:54,257
From now on, I'll do this job!

198
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,380
Please go ahead.

199
00:09:58,950 --> 00:09:59,830
Please go ahead.

200
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:24,740
Mr. Pei,

201
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,590
what are you up to this time around?

202
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:28,620
Cheh.

203
00:10:30,380 --> 00:10:32,110
Mr. Pei, I'm curious as to

204
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:34,500
when you'll get back on track again.

205
00:10:56,857 --> 00:10:58,380
Come on, let's play two more rounds.

206
00:10:58,380 --> 00:10:59,110
Ten more rounds.

207
00:10:59,110 --> 00:10:59,590
Sure.

208
00:10:59,590 --> 00:11:00,391
See if you can win.

209
00:11:00,413 --> 00:11:01,380
No problem.

210
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:10,990
This...

211
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:12,900
Does Tengda have
some kind of fairy godmother?

212
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:13,990
Lv,

213
00:11:14,260 --> 00:11:15,900
does someone have a crush on you?

214
00:11:16,140 --> 00:11:16,990
No way.

215
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:20,190
Obviously not.

216
00:11:20,190 --> 00:11:20,780
Look.

217
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:22,950
Unless she has a crush on both of us.

218
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:24,350
Morning, Lin Wan.

219
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:25,140
Morning.

220
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:29,230
Who arranged all my figures so neatly?

221
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,940
(Neck Support Patch)

222
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:32,830
Who got me all these

223
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:34,190
neck and back support patches?

224
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:38,260
Who made me this goji berry tea?

225
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:40,590
Our workspace is so clean and neat.

226
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:41,830
I thought our janitor

227
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:43,070
wasn't a J person.

228
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,990
Did we get someone new?

229
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:44,780
I don't think so.

230
00:11:44,780 --> 00:11:46,140
Someone refilled the cat food as well.

231
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:47,570
Someone cleaned the cat's bed as well.

232
00:11:48,620 --> 00:11:49,620
It was Mr. Pei.

233
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:53,740
Mr. Pei?

234
00:11:54,020 --> 00:11:55,710
He thought

235
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:57,110
the office was too messy.

236
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,860
That's why he cleaned it up.

237
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:02,710
How could we make Mr. Pei do that?

238
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:04,380
We have to do that ourselves.

239
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:06,070
I have a suggestion.

240
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:07,620
From now on,

241
00:12:07,620 --> 00:12:09,780
let's do a thorough spring cleaning.

242
00:12:09,990 --> 00:12:10,991
We mustn't let Mr. Pei

243
00:12:10,991 --> 00:12:12,590
worry about these minor matters anymore.

244
00:12:12,613 --> 00:12:13,230
Don't you agree?

245
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:14,020
Yeah.

246
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:14,710
You have a point.

247
00:12:14,710 --> 00:12:16,590
I'm not used to
having such a clean desk.

248
00:12:17,620 --> 00:12:20,860
(Today, Eternal Reincarnation,
the major game developed by Sky Fire,)

249
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:22,780
(is available for purchase.)

250
00:12:23,902 --> 00:12:26,210
(Eternal Reincarnation's Results Await)
(Eternal Reincarnation is a masterpiece)

251
00:12:26,213 --> 00:12:27,710
(crafted by Sky Fire
using five years.)

252
00:12:27,857 --> 00:12:29,990
(Sky Fire has truly spared
no expenses this time.)

253
00:12:30,740 --> 00:12:33,260
(But as for its result,
we still have to wait and see.)

254
00:12:33,324 --> 00:12:35,213
(Try Eternal Reincarnation together)
(Those who haven't played it yet, take note.)

255
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:37,629
(Now, Eternal Reincarnation
has an all-new voice-based gameplay.)

256
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:39,110
(It's something
you have to try for yourself.)

257
00:12:39,110 --> 00:12:40,110
(Hurry and join me.)

258
00:12:40,146 --> 00:12:41,230
(Trying Sky Fire's new game,
Eternal Reincarnation)

259
00:12:41,230 --> 00:12:42,860
(Eternal Reincarnation.)

260
00:12:42,860 --> 00:12:44,990
(Just that name alone
is attractive enough.)

261
00:12:45,035 --> 00:12:47,350
(Cool Trailer = Big-Budget Game)
(The trailers were pretty cool.)

262
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:48,470
(I feel like Eternal Reincarnation)

263
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:49,470
(should be the most expensive)

264
00:12:49,470 --> 00:12:51,391
(locally-developed video games
in recent years.)

265
00:12:57,524 --> 00:13:00,260
(Eternal Reincarnation is Sky Fire's
heartfelt creation.)

266
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:02,235
(It represents
the highest standards of Fuhui.)

267
00:13:02,235 --> 00:13:04,991
(It was masterfully crafted by their
team of experts over five years.)

268
00:13:04,991 --> 00:13:06,900
(An international version will
be released simultaneously)

269
00:13:06,902 --> 00:13:08,191
(and be introduced to the world.)

270
00:13:08,326 --> 00:13:09,446
Fuhui still thinks

271
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,989
that we've invested too much money
in Eternal Reincarnation.

272
00:13:11,990 --> 00:13:13,500
But they have no idea

273
00:13:13,780 --> 00:13:14,740
that this game

274
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:16,230
will surely succeed.

275
00:13:16,457 --> 00:13:18,830
We spent three times
Tengda's development cost to develop it.

276
00:13:18,830 --> 00:13:20,190
And, it has the same gameplay.

277
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:21,430
Tengda

278
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:23,710
is no match for us.

279
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,110
Yeah.

280
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:26,430
Mr. Zhou, under your management,

281
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:28,620
it'll definitely achieve success.

282
00:13:29,013 --> 00:13:30,170
Let's forget about all else.

283
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:31,620
The art style alone

284
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:32,830
is world-class.

285
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:34,302
By then, if we join hands

286
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:35,950
with the ACG (Anime, Comic, Game) circle,

287
00:13:35,950 --> 00:13:38,190
the character skins
will surely sell like hotcakes.

288
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:39,590
Mr. Zhou,

289
00:13:39,590 --> 00:13:40,830
I'm sure we can shut

290
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:42,500
the HQ up with this.

291
00:13:48,130 --> 00:13:51,270
(To be honest,
this looks kind of familiar.)

292
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:55,500
Check out the trending topics
on your phone.

293
00:13:56,257 --> 00:13:56,950
I'll take a look.

294
00:13:59,146 --> 00:14:00,900
Eternal Reincarnation
is one of the trending topics.

295
00:14:00,900 --> 00:14:01,710
Really?

296
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:02,350
Let me see.

297
00:14:07,350 --> 00:14:08,070
Mr. Zhou.

298
00:14:08,590 --> 00:14:09,230
Mr. Zhou.

299
00:14:09,230 --> 00:14:10,070
You forgot to knock.

300
00:14:17,740 --> 00:14:18,380
Come in.

301
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:20,710
Mr. Zhou.

302
00:14:20,768 --> 00:14:21,880
People on the internet said

303
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:24,070
that Eternal Reincarnation
resembled Returning to Shore.

304
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,724
Now, it's already
one of the trending topics.

305
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:28,380
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

306
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:34,070
This isn't a huge deal.

307
00:14:34,830 --> 00:14:36,430
Just push it down and be done with it.

308
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,900
(Eternal Reincarnation
Is Accused of Plagiarism)

309
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:53,660
Find Meng Chang.

310
00:14:53,968 --> 00:14:56,080
What's the point of spending
tens of millions

311
00:14:56,124 --> 00:14:57,090
on advertising on them?

312
00:14:57,124 --> 00:14:58,368
Tell him to manage public opinion.

313
00:14:58,391 --> 00:14:58,940
Understood.

314
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:10,230
(Eternal Reincarnation is much better
than Returning to Shore.)

315
00:15:10,230 --> 00:15:12,190
(The art style of Eternal Reincarnation
is clearly better.)

316
00:15:12,190 --> 00:15:13,500
(The worldview of Eternal Reincarnation)

317
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,430
(is much more creative.)

318
00:15:14,430 --> 00:15:15,702
(The plot is very interesting.)

319
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:29,380
(Special Assistant Office)

320
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:34,470
Hailu.

321
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,500
Wait.

322
00:15:36,950 --> 00:15:37,660
What's the matter?

323
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:39,190
Did Mr. Pei clean our office

324
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:40,860
with only that intention in mind?

325
00:15:41,830 --> 00:15:43,430
Before this, he vanished,

326
00:15:43,546 --> 00:15:45,860
joined Sky Fire, and even
worked as a designated driver.

327
00:15:45,860 --> 00:15:48,110
His actions have been irregular.

328
00:15:48,540 --> 00:15:50,190
Are you guys hiding any secret plans

329
00:15:50,190 --> 00:15:51,110
from us?

330
00:15:54,280 --> 00:15:55,780
Hurry and check out the trending topics.

331
00:15:55,780 --> 00:15:57,830
Sky Fire is first
on the trending topics.

332
00:15:58,430 --> 00:15:58,900
But why?

333
00:15:58,900 --> 00:15:59,900
On the trending again?

334
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,230
I thought they suppressed the news.

335
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:03,140
No. They're complaining about
Eternal Reincarnation's quality.

336
00:16:03,140 --> 00:16:05,260
People are criticizing them
for posting misleading trailers.

337
00:16:05,260 --> 00:16:06,660
The game was poorly made.

338
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,660
Plenty of players
are asking for a refund.

339
00:16:08,660 --> 00:16:10,190
I already expected that to happen.

340
00:16:10,190 --> 00:16:11,299
Look at the mess they're in.

341
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,213
And they're still
trying to pin the blame on us.

342
00:16:13,213 --> 00:16:14,140
They deserve this.

343
00:16:14,235 --> 00:16:15,860
Their reputation has indeed been ruined.

344
00:16:15,860 --> 00:16:17,860
(Trash game. Shut it down.)
Now, they can't suppress it anymore.

345
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,310
(Poorly made! Give me a refund!)
It's a total collapse.

346
00:16:19,310 --> 00:16:20,500
(The trailers were lies!
Close down Sky Fire! Give me a refund!)

347
00:16:21,791 --> 00:16:23,368
What's the point of hiring you guys?

348
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:24,900
All of you are freeloaders!

349
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:25,540
Oh no.

350
00:16:25,540 --> 00:16:27,110
Mr. Zhou has lost it again.

351
00:16:27,110 --> 00:16:28,590
Brace yourself for tough times ahead.

352
00:16:29,110 --> 00:16:30,020
I told you guys already.

353
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:32,260
Eternal Reincarnation would
get into trouble eventually.

354
00:16:32,260 --> 00:16:33,430
Hush. Stop it.

355
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:34,430
Return to work.

356
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:38,140
You can't even do such a simple task.

357
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:39,500
Useless fools.

358
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:46,990
(The trailers were lies!)

359
00:16:46,990 --> 00:16:48,830
(I heard that Sky Fire
has fallen from grace.)

360
00:16:48,830 --> 00:16:50,350
(They invested too much money
in the previous games.)

361
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:51,540
(And they didn't make enough
to cover the cost.)

362
00:16:51,540 --> 00:16:53,099
(Give me a refund!)

363
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:53,724
(Refund!)

364
00:16:53,768 --> 00:16:54,860
Is Meng Chang dead?

365
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:57,590
Can't he even manage public opinion?

366
00:16:57,590 --> 00:16:58,860
Tell him to give us a refund!

367
00:16:58,946 --> 00:16:59,860
Meng Chang said

368
00:16:59,968 --> 00:17:02,124
he tried suppressing it a few times,
but to no avail.

369
00:17:02,124 --> 00:17:03,350
No matter how high the budget is,

370
00:17:03,350 --> 00:17:04,850
they can't withstand spending like this.

371
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:06,191
Moreover, the game was rushed out

372
00:17:06,546 --> 00:17:08,946
after the staff expansion
to meet the early launch deadline.

373
00:17:09,470 --> 00:17:11,630
Now that more and more players
have tried the game,

374
00:17:11,820 --> 00:17:13,230
there's no way to suppress the news.

375
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:15,430
Increase our budget.

376
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:17,150
Tell everyone

377
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:18,580
to prepare for combat.

378
00:17:18,580 --> 00:17:19,990
Get the situation under control

379
00:17:19,990 --> 00:17:21,280
no matter how much it'll cost us!

380
00:17:21,780 --> 00:17:22,710
Get it under control!

381
00:17:23,230 --> 00:17:23,990
Understood.

382
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:45,980
(Fuhui)

383
00:17:49,630 --> 00:17:50,300
Come in.

384
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:56,190
Mr. Li, Sky Fire seeks to
apply for additional funding

385
00:17:56,190 --> 00:17:57,870
for their game, Eternal Reincarnation.

386
00:17:59,710 --> 00:18:01,230
This is the cost estimation report.

387
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:04,230
They want additional funding?

388
00:18:04,502 --> 00:18:06,230
I thought the game
was already completed.

389
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:07,150
Indeed.

390
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,670
It's precisely because
the game's current download numbers

391
00:18:09,670 --> 00:18:10,880
have plummeted dramatically.

392
00:18:10,946 --> 00:18:13,270
So they wish to increase
the funding for promotional purposes.

393
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:14,230
However,

394
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:15,870
online reviews of the game

395
00:18:16,340 --> 00:18:17,670
have all been negative.

396
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:18,990
Based on our observation,

397
00:18:18,990 --> 00:18:20,060
this emerging trend

398
00:18:20,260 --> 00:18:21,740
might affect Fuhui.

399
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:26,740
Sky Fire...

400
00:18:27,324 --> 00:18:28,910
They did develop some excellent games

401
00:18:29,230 --> 00:18:31,230
in the past few years.

402
00:18:32,213 --> 00:18:34,150
But they've invested
all of their resources

403
00:18:35,150 --> 00:18:37,230
into marketing in recent years.

404
00:18:37,990 --> 00:18:39,230
Their so-called viral games

405
00:18:39,457 --> 00:18:41,550
were an attempt
to deceive themselves and the public.

406
00:18:42,430 --> 00:18:43,630
If this keeps up,

407
00:18:44,150 --> 00:18:46,910
the HQ might be affected.

408
00:18:48,230 --> 00:18:49,470
Understood, Mr. Li.

409
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:51,470
I'll instruct the legal department

410
00:18:51,710 --> 00:18:52,870
to prepare an announcement

411
00:18:52,870 --> 00:18:54,857
and implement risk mitigation
measures in advance.

412
00:19:20,857 --> 00:19:22,260
Everyone, prepare for combat.

413
00:19:22,540 --> 00:19:23,910
For Eternal Reincarnation,

414
00:19:23,910 --> 00:19:25,020
let's give it one more shot!

415
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:26,020
I'll only say this.

416
00:19:26,191 --> 00:19:27,235
For the sake of the company,

417
00:19:27,235 --> 00:19:28,990
only success is allowed!

418
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:29,740
Understood?

419
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:31,124
- Understood.
- Understood.

420
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:37,368
How are the online remarks?

421
00:19:38,835 --> 00:19:40,100
(They spent five years developing it?)

422
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,257
(More like ten days.)

423
00:19:41,257 --> 00:19:42,950
(I see their ads all the time
when I scroll my phone.)

424
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:44,150
(As a loyal fan of Sky Fire,)

425
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:45,710
(I'm truly disappointed.)

426
00:19:45,710 --> 00:19:46,990
(It's not an issue with
the graphics and hardware.)

427
00:19:46,990 --> 00:19:47,540
(It's the gameplay.)

428
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:49,500
Keep their remarks under control. Do it!

429
00:19:54,740 --> 00:19:56,020
What's going on?

430
00:19:56,740 --> 00:19:57,390
Zhao,

431
00:19:57,670 --> 00:19:59,870
the online backlash against Sky Fire
is running high.

432
00:19:59,870 --> 00:20:01,820
I'm sure you know as well.
Can't keep them under control.

433
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:03,020
Even so, you have to do it!

434
00:20:03,020 --> 00:20:04,740
Why are you telling me all this?

435
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:07,150
We've been at it nonstop
for 24 hours straight.

436
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:08,580
It's not like we get to determine

437
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:10,013
when we can keep them under control.

438
00:20:10,013 --> 00:20:11,710
And, the budget isn't enough.

439
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:13,820
Stop talking about the budget.

440
00:20:14,020 --> 00:20:15,230
I've already given you plenty.

441
00:20:15,230 --> 00:20:16,260
Hand that to me.

442
00:20:18,540 --> 00:20:20,150
Must you drink coffee now?

443
00:20:21,710 --> 00:20:22,710
Get to work!

444
00:20:23,035 --> 00:20:24,280
Don't even try to pick it up!

445
00:20:26,020 --> 00:20:26,740
Zhao,

446
00:20:26,740 --> 00:20:28,150
what's going on over there?

447
00:20:28,150 --> 00:20:30,020
Everyone is highly emotional right now.

448
00:20:30,470 --> 00:20:31,300
I didn't hire you

449
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,300
to create excuses.

450
00:20:32,300 --> 00:20:33,591
I hired you to solve my issues.

451
00:20:33,613 --> 00:20:35,300
That's your job, you know?

452
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,060
I know it's my job,

453
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:37,950
but I can't just

454
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:39,340
work for nothing.

455
00:20:41,780 --> 00:20:42,300
Fine.

456
00:20:42,746 --> 00:20:44,020
I'll tell Mr. Zhou about it.

457
00:20:45,340 --> 00:20:49,420
(Eternal Reincarnation
No Failure Allowed)

458
00:21:02,140 --> 00:21:09,300
(Eternal Reincarnation
Reputation Defense Proposal)

459
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:18,300
(Sky Fire Tower)

460
00:21:28,102 --> 00:21:29,870
It's been five days
since I last went home.

461
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:31,470
My clothes stink.

462
00:21:34,260 --> 00:21:36,390
I think I've lost my sense of smell.

463
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,470
It's fine even if it stinks.

464
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:39,540
Everyone stinks anyway.

465
00:21:40,990 --> 00:21:43,710
We've been doing this for 45 days.

466
00:21:43,710 --> 00:21:45,990
Even a corpse
would've decomposed by now.

467
00:22:08,950 --> 00:22:10,020
Chen, what's wrong?

468
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:10,740
Chen!

469
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:11,470
Chen, what's wrong?

470
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:11,950
Chen!

471
00:22:11,950 --> 00:22:12,870
Call 120!

472
00:22:13,670 --> 00:22:14,500
Chen, are you okay?

473
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,870
Chen, wake up!

474
00:22:15,870 --> 00:22:16,630
Wake up!

475
00:22:16,630 --> 00:22:17,470
Call the ambulance!

476
00:22:17,990 --> 00:22:18,780
Chen!

477
00:22:19,791 --> 00:22:21,820
(Sky Fire)
We gave Meng Chang additional budget.

478
00:22:21,857 --> 00:22:23,950
They're trying their best
to manage the situation.

479
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:25,810
The online haters are no big deal.

480
00:22:25,810 --> 00:22:27,635
But the thing is,
we've been losing players.

481
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:28,500
And,

482
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:32,710
no new players are joining the fray.

483
00:22:32,710 --> 00:22:33,820
Slowly!

484
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:37,740
Chen?

485
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:38,540
Are you okay?

486
00:22:38,540 --> 00:22:39,150
What's wrong?

487
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:40,470
Do you feel better?

488
00:22:40,710 --> 00:22:41,950
Did you forget about work?

489
00:22:42,100 --> 00:22:42,910
Lend us a hand.

490
00:22:42,910 --> 00:22:44,260
We're on high alert.

491
00:22:44,390 --> 00:22:45,710
We're on high alert!

492
00:22:46,260 --> 00:22:47,540
Has anyone ever considered

493
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:48,910
the company's interest at all?

494
00:22:48,991 --> 00:22:51,020
Just look at the state
Eternal Reincarnation is in.

495
00:22:51,190 --> 00:22:52,630
Have you guys ever considered that?

496
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:54,470
What the heck are you guys doing?

497
00:22:54,470 --> 00:22:55,500
Work is still in session!

498
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,670
Are you playing over there?

499
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:58,630
Mr. Zhao, we've been working overtime
for the past 45 days.

500
00:22:58,635 --> 00:22:59,630
Chen is about to collapse!

501
00:22:59,630 --> 00:23:01,191
If you can't withstand this, go home!

502
00:23:01,710 --> 00:23:02,430
Chen,

503
00:23:03,300 --> 00:23:04,390
how old are you?

504
00:23:04,813 --> 00:23:07,230
If you're that old, and you can't
withstand the workload,

505
00:23:07,230 --> 00:23:08,813
you should go home as soon as possible.

506
00:23:08,857 --> 00:23:10,260
Why are you even here?

507
00:23:10,990 --> 00:23:11,910
Mr. Zhou, Mr. Zhao,

508
00:23:12,260 --> 00:23:13,710
I'm fine.

509
00:23:13,710 --> 00:23:14,710
I can do this.

510
00:23:17,835 --> 00:23:19,950
You have been
working overtime all this while.

511
00:23:20,013 --> 00:23:21,502
I'm sure it's been tough on you guys.

512
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:23,102
I'm sure you have plenty of complaints.

513
00:23:23,740 --> 00:23:25,630
Let me tell you guys

514
00:23:26,260 --> 00:23:28,300
what I think about my work.

515
00:23:29,780 --> 00:23:32,230
Some of you might say

516
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:33,540
that you've devoted a lot of time

517
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:34,990
and efforts

518
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:36,400
for the sake of the projects

519
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:37,450
and the company.

520
00:23:37,835 --> 00:23:40,020
I suppose you think
that it's been tough on you.

521
00:23:41,710 --> 00:23:43,470
But just look at me.

522
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:44,990
- Mr. Zhou.
- Mr. Zhou.

523
00:23:44,990 --> 00:23:45,740
Look at Chen.

524
00:23:45,740 --> 00:23:47,150
He fainted just now.

525
00:23:49,190 --> 00:23:50,950
Just look at me.

526
00:23:51,260 --> 00:23:52,630
I, Zhou Muyan,

527
00:23:53,190 --> 00:23:56,020
treated this company as my own home.

528
00:23:57,020 --> 00:24:00,020
I knew you guys didn't leave
for the past 45 days.

529
00:24:00,020 --> 00:24:01,950
I did the same

530
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:03,060
as you guys!

531
00:24:03,060 --> 00:24:05,257
I pulled countless all-nighters,
just like you all!

532
00:24:05,260 --> 00:24:06,910
Go and inspect my office if you like.

533
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:09,470
The number of coffee and tea I took,

534
00:24:09,470 --> 00:24:10,910
it was just as much as you all!

535
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,020
Trust me!

536
00:24:30,190 --> 00:24:32,430
If any one of you

537
00:24:32,740 --> 00:24:33,990
wants to leave Sky Fire,

538
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:35,630
scram right now!

539
00:24:35,780 --> 00:24:36,540
Get lost!

540
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:37,740
I won't stop you!

541
00:24:39,670 --> 00:24:40,857
If you leave,

542
00:24:40,857 --> 00:24:42,910
you'll starve to death on the streets!

543
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:45,150
Don't you know the situation out there?

544
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,580
Do you know
how many people out there are queuing

545
00:24:47,580 --> 00:24:50,300
just to get a job?

546
00:24:51,910 --> 00:24:53,430
We don't lack any of you!

547
