Sky Fire anyway.

823
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:09,350
Mr. Li Jr.,

824
00:36:10,220 --> 00:36:11,413
Sky Fire has made

825
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:13,580
significant contributions
to Fuhui after all.

826
00:36:13,580 --> 00:36:14,220
Don't you agree?

827
00:36:15,750 --> 00:36:17,430
But all gatherings must come to an end.

828
00:36:17,430 --> 00:36:19,350
Nothing lasts forever.

829
00:36:19,350 --> 00:36:19,990
Don't you agree?

830
00:36:19,990 --> 00:36:20,830
Mr. Li Jr.,

831
00:36:21,270 --> 00:36:23,100
what do you mean by that?

832
00:36:23,990 --> 00:36:24,750
Mr. Zhou,

833
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:26,790
I'm just relaying Dad's message to you.

834
00:36:28,990 --> 00:36:29,700
But Mr. Zhou,

835
00:36:29,830 --> 00:36:31,580
I understand your feelings completely.

836
00:36:31,700 --> 00:36:33,140
After all, you guys have made

837
00:36:33,140 --> 00:36:34,568
significant contributions to Fuhui.

838
00:36:34,568 --> 00:36:36,500
And, there's another path you can take.

839
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:42,900
(Sky Fire)

840
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:47,700
Alright.

841
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:49,100
Next,

842
00:36:49,270 --> 00:36:50,620
I'll host this meeting.

843
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:54,100
Mr. Pei is willing to acquire Sky Fire
on behalf of Tengda.

844
00:36:54,324 --> 00:36:56,620
He'll take over everything
that belongs to Sky Fire.

845
00:36:57,750 --> 00:36:58,430
Of course,

846
00:36:58,430 --> 00:36:59,470
that includes you as well.

847
00:36:59,660 --> 00:37:00,540
Pei Qian.

848
00:37:00,768 --> 00:37:02,700
You don't need
to take such a huge detour

849
00:37:02,700 --> 00:37:04,350
just to humiliate me!

850
00:37:04,540 --> 00:37:05,430
Listen up!

851
00:37:05,540 --> 00:37:06,540
I quit!

852
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:07,680
In your current situation,

853
00:37:07,680 --> 00:37:08,968
you won't find a better choice.

854
00:37:08,991 --> 00:37:10,100
Tengda is able to offer you

855
00:37:10,100 --> 00:37:11,750
the top salary in the industry.

856
00:37:23,910 --> 00:37:26,060
I'm a professional manager.

857
00:37:26,990 --> 00:37:28,310
Everything is negotiable.

858
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,430
You're a professional indeed.

859
00:37:36,220 --> 00:37:37,220
What about me?

860
00:37:41,270 --> 00:37:42,100
Zhao,

861
00:37:42,700 --> 00:37:43,660
I'm thirsty.

862
00:37:43,660 --> 00:37:44,700
Buy me a cup of coffee.

863
00:37:46,820 --> 00:37:49,300
(One Month Later)

864
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:53,390
Ms. Lin Wan.

865
00:37:53,620 --> 00:37:55,310
We renamed Sky Fire to Late Departure

866
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:57,100
in hopes that you all

867
00:37:57,100 --> 00:37:59,124
could get used to Tengda's
slower working pace.

868
00:37:59,146 --> 00:37:59,990
We respected most of

869
00:37:59,990 --> 00:38:01,180
the staff members' wishes

870
00:38:01,180 --> 00:38:03,413
and allowed them to continue
working remotely from Xinyang.

871
00:38:03,540 --> 00:38:05,180
You all are willing to relocate

872
00:38:05,180 --> 00:38:07,180
to Jinchuan just to work at our HQ.

873
00:38:07,390 --> 00:38:08,540
It's been tough on you all.

874
00:38:08,540 --> 00:38:10,140
- Not at all!
- Not at all!

875
00:38:10,140 --> 00:38:11,830
All moving expenses

876
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:13,180
will be covered by Tengda.

877
00:38:13,180 --> 00:38:14,650
If you have any reimbursement claims,

878
00:38:14,657 --> 00:38:16,280
please send them
to the Finance Department.

879
00:38:16,324 --> 00:38:17,540
- Okay!
- Okay!

880
00:38:18,350 --> 00:38:20,310
Ms. Lin Wan, we already have it easy.

881
00:38:20,310 --> 00:38:21,310
It's not tough at all.

882
00:38:21,310 --> 00:38:23,220
Tengda hired so many helpers
just to help us move.

883
00:38:23,220 --> 00:38:25,020
We didn't even
need to move a single thing.

884
00:38:25,020 --> 00:38:26,390
You also provided us
with employee dormitories.

885
00:38:26,390 --> 00:38:28,020
And our unit has two bedrooms
and one hall each.

886
00:38:28,020 --> 00:38:30,060
Yeah. It's even larger than
the unit I used to rent.

887
00:38:30,060 --> 00:38:31,140
You can resume your work.

888
00:38:31,140 --> 00:38:31,950
Get used to it first.

889
00:38:31,950 --> 00:38:33,310
- Okay.
- Thank you, Ms. Lin Wan.

890
00:38:33,310 --> 00:38:34,350
Thank you, Ms. Lin.

891
00:38:35,500 --> 00:38:36,140
Let's go.

892
00:38:36,140 --> 00:38:37,180
This is great.

893
00:38:37,180 --> 00:38:45,060
(Late Departure Sdudio)

894
00:38:54,540 --> 00:38:56,580
(Xu)

895
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:57,830
(What a fulfilling day.)

896
00:38:57,830 --> 00:38:59,020
(Since it's still overtime,)

897
00:38:59,020 --> 00:39:00,790
(let's take a sip of coffee first.)

898
00:39:05,350 --> 00:39:07,100
(Moments, The Cyclist)
(Message delivered.)

899
00:39:07,100 --> 00:39:08,870
(One more message available.)

900
00:39:09,635 --> 00:39:10,900
(Shrimp)
(Dinner at my workplace.)

901
00:39:10,900 --> 00:39:12,390
(Supper will be provided after dinner.)

902
00:39:12,390 --> 00:39:14,350
(There's even breakfast after supper.)

903
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:24,950
Once I'm done here,

904
00:39:24,950 --> 00:39:27,390
shift the sticker to the other side

905
00:39:27,390 --> 00:39:28,830
and change the filming angle.

906
00:39:28,830 --> 00:39:30,750
This way, no one can tell
it's the same cup.

907
00:39:31,140 --> 00:39:32,540
That's a brilliant idea.

908
00:39:32,568 --> 00:39:34,213
A cup of coffee is expensive nowadays.

909
00:39:34,257 --> 00:39:36,280
We can share one cup
to post on our Moments.

910
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,580
This way, we can save some money.

911
00:39:37,580 --> 00:39:38,500
Yeah.

912
00:39:40,100 --> 00:39:41,580
Ms. Lin just liked my post.

913
00:39:43,180 --> 00:39:44,390
I told you already.

914
00:39:44,990 --> 00:39:47,140
I'm sure she didn't want us
to get off work.

915
00:39:47,140 --> 00:39:49,910
She just wanted to see
if we were working overtime at home.

916
00:39:50,660 --> 00:39:51,790
It's a bait-and-switch.

917
00:39:51,800 --> 00:39:53,180
It's the oldest trick in the book.

918
00:39:53,180 --> 00:39:53,660
Yeah.

919
00:39:53,660 --> 00:39:54,540
She'll sack anyone

920
00:39:54,540 --> 00:39:55,830
who doesn't work overtime.

921
00:39:56,270 --> 00:39:58,060
I don't think Mr. Pei and Lin Wan

922
00:39:58,060 --> 00:39:59,140
are like that.

923
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:01,470
Anyway, all bosses like it
when their employees work overtime.

924
00:40:01,470 --> 00:40:01,990
Am I right?

925
00:40:01,990 --> 00:40:02,620
Yeah.

926
00:40:05,020 --> 00:40:06,020
Why are the lights off?

927
00:40:06,580 --> 00:40:07,950
The lights are already out?

928
00:40:08,830 --> 00:40:10,870
Guys, sorry for the interruption.

929
00:40:10,870 --> 00:40:13,020
We sell coffee during the day
and alcohol at night.

930
00:40:13,020 --> 00:40:15,413
If you want to take pictures,
you can head to the cybercafe.

931
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:16,270
It's free.

932
00:40:16,660 --> 00:40:17,660
Thanks for the support.

933
00:40:17,660 --> 00:40:18,620
It's fine.

934
00:40:18,660 --> 00:40:19,620
This is great.

935
00:40:19,620 --> 00:40:21,280
We can take pictures
at two different venues

936
00:40:21,324 --> 00:40:22,180
for the price of one.

937
00:40:22,830 --> 00:40:23,660
Let's go.

938
00:40:24,020 --> 00:40:24,660
Let's go.

939
00:40:24,660 --> 00:40:25,350
Great idea.

940
00:40:25,350 --> 00:40:26,660
It does look pretty good.

941
00:40:26,660 --> 00:40:27,899
Alright. Let's head over there.

942
00:40:27,900 --> 00:40:29,500
You two won't need to spend
a single cent.

943
00:40:29,500 --> 00:40:30,580
Take pictures for tomorrow.

944
00:40:30,580 --> 00:40:32,020
Why didn't she like my post?

945
00:40:32,020 --> 00:40:33,235
I don't know. Did you post it?

946
00:40:33,257 --> 00:40:34,100
Yeah, I did.

947
00:40:34,100 --> 00:40:35,280
I suppose she didn't see it.

948
00:40:35,324 --> 00:40:36,580
But I did work overtime.

949
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:47,390
Mr. Pei,

950
00:40:48,020 --> 00:40:49,540
I've encountered some issues

951
00:40:49,540 --> 00:40:51,180
while managing our personnel.

952
00:40:51,390 --> 00:40:52,750
May I seek your guidance?

953
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:58,910
They're still heavily influenced
by Sky Fire's work culture.

954
00:40:58,910 --> 00:41:00,660
I feel like they're bots.

955
00:41:00,660 --> 00:41:03,100
I don't know what to do with them.

956
00:41:03,620 --> 00:41:05,702
I understand. I understand
their feelings completely.

957
00:41:05,830 --> 00:41:07,180
You see, it's not their fault.

958
00:41:07,470 --> 00:41:09,830
They're too used
to their previous company.

959
00:41:10,270 --> 00:41:12,310
The institutional management of Sky Fire

960
00:41:12,310 --> 00:41:14,310
is extremely damaging to people.

961
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:17,100
Yeah. If they work for a company
like that for a long time,

962
00:41:17,100 --> 00:41:18,102
they'll start to doubt

963
00:41:18,102 --> 00:41:20,830
whether or not they deserve
to have a normal working environment,

964
00:41:20,830 --> 00:41:22,870
a normal working pace,

965
00:41:22,870 --> 00:41:23,790
and a normal life

966
00:41:23,790 --> 00:41:25,580
after work.

967
00:41:27,620 --> 00:41:28,220
So,

968
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:30,350
we have to help them
get over that mental barrier.

969
00:41:32,390 --> 00:41:33,390
But how?

970
00:41:48,060 --> 00:41:51,140
♪We're dancing on a broken beat♪

971
00:41:51,140 --> 00:41:53,980
♪Exhaustion written all over us♪

972
00:41:54,420 --> 00:41:57,940
♪Watching as the colors fade away♪

973
00:41:57,940 --> 00:41:59,580
♪Your silence♪

974
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:04,340
♪It's a fortress and I'm running out
of ways to get to your heart♪

975
00:42:04,340 --> 00:42:08,580
♪It's harder to see you
when I get too close♪

976
00:42:10,180 --> 00:42:12,900
♪The buzzing in the air♪

977
00:42:13,260 --> 00:42:16,940
♪The static's getting louder♪

978
00:42:17,100 --> 00:42:18,940
♪Shadows dancing♪

979
00:42:18,940 --> 00:42:21,060
♪Say you've had enough♪

980
00:42:21,700 --> 00:42:23,220
♪I say I've had enough♪

981
00:42:25,820 --> 00:42:28,980
♪I struggle on, holding back the clouds♪

982
00:42:28,980 --> 00:42:30,980
♪With the city inside♪

983
00:42:30,980 --> 00:42:32,860
♪Say you're holding on♪

984
00:42:34,020 --> 00:42:35,780
♪I say I'm holding on♪

985
00:42:37,220 --> 00:42:41,540
♪Can you see the weight behind
this pain, this smile I'm wearing♪

986
00:42:41,540 --> 00:42:43,460
♪I'll never let it show♪

987
00:42:44,340 --> 00:42:47,660
♪Curating the highlights in my story♪

988
00:42:47,660 --> 00:42:51,100
♪Filter out shaky frames from my glory♪

989
00:42:51,100 --> 00:42:54,220
♪All this noise and mess♪

990
00:42:54,220 --> 00:42:55,620
♪Needs some stillness♪

991
00:42:55,620 --> 00:42:58,580
♪Say you're holding on♪

992
00:42:58,580 --> 00:43:01,020
♪I say I'm holding on♪

993
00:43:02,660 --> 00:43:05,820
♪If you need to say goodbye,
just let it out, baby♪

994
00:43:05,820 --> 00:43:07,820
♪I'll get by♪

995
00:43:07,820 --> 00:43:10,100
♪Say you've had enough♪

996
00:43:10,900 --> 00:43:12,500
♪I say I've had enough♪

997
00:43:14,220 --> 00:43:18,380
♪If you're bearing the ache
of every single breath you take♪

998
00:43:18,380 --> 00:43:20,420
♪And I'm watching him escape♪

999
00:43:21,580 --> 00:43:24,580
♪I'm falling through the space
into the silence you make♪

1000
00:43:24,580 --> 00:43:28,180
♪Just a flicker in the dark
and saying out your name♪

1001
00:43:28,180 --> 00:43:31,420
♪All this noise and mess♪

1002
00:43:31,420 --> 00:43:32,860
♪Needs some stillness♪

1003
00:43:32,860 --> 00:43:34,700
♪Say you're holding on♪

1004
00:43:35,900 --> 00:43:37,900
♪I say I'm holding on♪

1005
00:43:40,260 --> 00:43:41,300
♪Darling♪

1006
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:44,260
♪I'll gently feel your face♪

1007
00:43:44,260 --> 00:43:46,460
♪I'll reach you before dawn♪

1008
00:43:46,460 --> 00:43:50,460
♪I want you to keep believing♪

1009
00:43:52,620 --> 00:43:53,940
♪Darling♪

1010
00:43:53,940 --> 00:43:56,980
♪Let's take it slow and play our parts♪

1011
00:43:56,980 --> 00:43:58,020
♪And fool our hearts♪

1012
00:43:58,020 --> 00:44:05,220
♪In this static, this buzzing air♪
